import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='year', y='yield', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    median_yield = data['yield'].median()
    plt.axhline(y=median_yield, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Yield: {median_yield:.2f}')
    plt.legend()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.violinplot(x='variety', y='yield', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the yield vary across different varieties of barley?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Variety')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Varieties', labels=data['variety'].unique(), loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
